headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 28 points and matched a season high with 15 assists, and the Indiana Pacers recovered after blowing a 17-point third-quarter lead to beat the Houston Rockets 115-102 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton and the Pacers recover from blown lead, close out the Rockets 115-102

headlines.description: — Ja’Kobe Walter swished a contested 3-pointer with 0.5 seconds remaining and the Toronto Raptors edged the Orlando Magic 114-113 on Tuesday night after blowing a 12-point lead in the fourth...
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors rookie Ja’Kobe Walter hits 3 with 0.5 seconds left for 114-113 win over slumping Magic

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 26 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists for his seventh triple-double of the season, and the surging Milwaukee Bucks beat the Atlanta Hawks 127-121 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo posts triple-double as surging Bucks finish strong to beat Hawks 127-121

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 28 points and nine assists while running his personal record to 12-1 at Madison Square Garden, and the Golden State Warriors beat the New York Knicks 114-102 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 28, improves to 12-1 at Madison Square Garden as Warriors beat Knicks 114-102

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 28 points, Jarrett Allen added 25 points and 17 rebounds, and the NBA-best Cleveland Cavaliers won their 11th straight game, 139-117 over the Chicago Bulls on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 28 and NBA-best Cavs beat Bulls 139-117 for 11th straight win

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 18 points, Naz Reid added 23 and the Minnesota Timberwolves pulled away in the fourth quarter to beat the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers 126-112 on Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reid scores 23 as Wolves pull away in fourth to beat 76ers 126-112

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell had a career-high 37 points along with 10 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs rolled to a 127-113 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vassell's career-high 37 points lead Spurs past struggling Nets 127-113

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 34 points, Devin Booker added 17 and the Phoenix Suns rallied from a 23-point deficit late in the third quarter to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 119-117 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 34, Suns rally from 23-point deficit in 2nd half to beat the Clippers 119-117

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron scores 34 after historic 50,000th point, and Lakers beat Pelicans 136-115 for 7th straight W
